WEBVTT

00:03.810 --> 00:06.854
Welcome to the podcast for Perdido Bay Methodist Church.

00:07.555 --> 00:10.999
My name is Dudley and today is Monday, March 2nd.

00:11.861 --> 00:13.643
And our chapter is Matthew 22.

00:13.663 --> 00:17.328
And there are several things covered in this chapter.

00:18.049 --> 00:20.492
We see the parable of the wedding banquet.

00:21.033 --> 00:31.186
We see that the religious leaders continue to try to trap Jesus in his own words, but Jesus sees through their evil intent.

00:31.842 --> 00:36.468
first about taxes and then about marriage and the resurrection.

00:36.488 --> 00:46.800
One key statement that Jesus says here is that they were in error because they did not know the scriptures or the power of God.

00:48.282 --> 01:01.458
And to this, I pray, Lord, let us be a people who know your word and let us know your power, your life-changing, life-giving power that changes us

01:01.570 --> 01:05.474
for both now and this life, but for all of eternity.

01:06.455 --> 01:10.239
And the attempts to trap Jesus in his words continue.

01:11.100 --> 01:13.663
But then Jesus has a question of his own.

01:14.684 --> 01:18.949
Listen to this excerpt of the last part of Matthew 22.

01:19.009 --> 01:23.894
Teacher, which is the greatest commandment in the law.

01:24.815 --> 01:30.962
Jesus replied, love the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your mind.

01:31.426 --> 01:33.990
This is the first and greatest commandment.

01:34.991 --> 01:36.734
And the second is like it.

01:37.355 --> 01:38.777
Love your neighbor as yourself.

01:39.938 --> 01:43.684
All the law and the prophets hang on these two commandments.

01:45.266 --> 01:53.739
It seems no matter how much the enemies of Jesus tried to trick him or trap him in his words, it would never work.

01:54.560 --> 01:57.204
His wisdom is too great.

01:58.346 --> 01:58.706
But

01:59.362 --> 02:00.243
Do you know what else?

02:00.563 --> 02:12.195
His love for people is so great that he was willing to be that sacrifice, to give his life, to take that punishment, to bring peace between God and man.

02:13.636 --> 02:19.522
As we close our time today, I'm reminded of John the Baptist preparing the way for Jesus to come.

02:20.704 --> 02:27.090
And then I see that Jesus is preparing the way of salvation for us and for others

02:27.298 --> 02:56.594
to come to the Father so that our plan should be to prepare the way for others to hear this message, this great news, by loving and serving, teaching, and even correcting so that others can experience life change here, but so that they can experience eternal life that comes from the Father, the Son, and the Holy Spirit.

02:58.018 --> 02:58.995
Have a blessed day.

